description.en: The qoo-ontology is a lightweight ontology based on IoT-Lite and SSN to describe and characterized sensors, observations and Quality of Observation (QoO).

comment.en: Circle coverage it needs the location of the sensor as the centre of the circle and the radius as a DataProperty.
The coverage of an IoT device (i.e. a temperature sensor inside a room has a coverage of that room).

Teh coverage is made up by giving two points which are the oposite corners of a rentangle.
The coverage is made up by linking several points by strait lines.
